53:28.620 --> 53:30.103
♪

53:30.206 --> 53:31.344
[chuckles]

53:31.448 --> 53:33.862
I love this movie.

53:36.896 --> 53:39.206
- Listen, uh--
- Huh?

53:39.310 --> 53:41.586
- We had a lot to drink,

53:41.689 --> 53:44.068
and things got a little
out of control, you know?

53:44.172 --> 53:47.862
And, you know,
if it's all the same to you,

53:47.965 --> 53:49.896
I'd prefer we just forget
the whole thing.

53:50.000 --> 53:51.068
- You want to forget it?
- Yeah.

53:51.172 --> 53:53.034
- Yeah.

53:53.137 --> 53:57.103
Well, maybe my emotions
got the best of me.

53:57.206 --> 53:59.034
- For good reason, you know?
I understand that.

53:59.137 --> 54:01.206
- You understand?
- Yeah.

54:01.310 --> 54:05.103
- Hey, hey, I--
I didn't mean to hit you.

54:05.206 --> 54:06.758
Huh?
- Yeah.

54:06.862 --> 54:08.655
- I mean, you jumped
the wrong way, and--

54:08.758 --> 54:10.758
- Exactly.
- I was coming to get you.

54:10.862 --> 54:12.068
I was a little worried,

54:12.172 --> 54:14.034
and you wouldn't have been
able to walk back, and--

54:14.137 --> 54:15.724
- Yeah, no way
I would have made it back.

54:15.827 --> 54:17.517
- Yeah. I mean,
you would have froze to death.

54:17.620 --> 54:19.275
- Right.

54:19.379 --> 54:22.034
- I saved your life.

54:23.172 --> 54:25.482
- Looks like I owe you one.
- Yeah.

54:25.586 --> 54:30.448
You want to call it even?
Huh?

54:30.551 --> 54:33.482
Yeah?
I got you some chow.

54:33.586 --> 54:36.586
[house warbling,
muffled crackling]

54:37.655 --> 54:41.862
Hey, listen,
I think I owe you the truth.

54:43.241 --> 54:46.000
- Truth about what?

54:50.862 --> 54:52.965
- Why I brought you out here.

54:53.068 --> 54:55.206
- I don't care.
I don't--I don't want to--

54:55.310 --> 54:58.103
- I was careful.
- What?

54:58.206 --> 55:01.000
- No one saw us leave together,
not really.

55:01.103 --> 55:03.689
I've been careful.

55:03.793 --> 55:05.413
- What are you talking about?

55:05.517 --> 55:07.103
- I want to help you.

55:07.206 --> 55:10.241
- Help me with what?

55:10.344 --> 55:13.000
- Your situation.

55:13.103 --> 55:15.034
- What situation?

55:15.137 --> 55:16.793
- Go ahead.
Dig in.

55:16.896 --> 55:20.655
[soft dramatic music]

55:20.758 --> 55:26.137
Why is it that you never got
promoted at Graco Z?

55:26.241 --> 55:28.275
♪

55:28.379 --> 55:29.724
You've been there
long enough, Wayne.

55:29.827 --> 55:34.379
A fucking monkey
could run that deck.

55:34.482 --> 55:38.586
And you barely making it out of
the infantry after nine years.

55:38.689 --> 55:41.586
Why is that?

55:41.689 --> 55:44.000
Huh?

55:44.103 --> 55:45.103
- I don't know
what you're talking about.

55:45.206 --> 55:49.413
- Two years vocational,

55:49.517 --> 55:51.344
getting groomed
for administrative salary,

55:51.448 --> 55:55.206
but you've been passed over

55:55.310 --> 55:58.103
time and time again,

55:58.206 --> 55:59.793
shafted by the same company

55:59.896 --> 56:04.241
that you've been
nothing but loyal to.

56:04.344 --> 56:05.413
- I don't know what this
has to do with anything--

56:05.517 --> 56:09.620
- All because
you took that money,

56:12.758 --> 56:14.310
The petty cash
off that delivery

56:14.413 --> 56:18.000
that you didn't think
anyone would notice.

56:18.103 --> 56:23.689
You saw a chance,
and you pocketed that cash.

56:23.793 --> 56:28.862
The only problem is
you got caught.

56:28.965 --> 56:32.344
And instead of charging you,
saving you the embarrassment,

56:32.448 --> 56:35.620
you got a slap on the wrist,

56:35.724 --> 56:37.000
shuffled back into
the machine shop

56:37.103 --> 56:41.413
for eternal blue-collar
wandering bliss.

56:41.517 --> 56:45.620
You risked it all and lost...

56:45.724 --> 56:48.655
for 850 bucks.

56:52.000 --> 56:53.137
- How the hell do you
know that?

56:53.241 --> 56:56.206
- Oh, Wayne, come on.

56:57.758 --> 57:02.413
My old man
owns the title company.

57:02.517 --> 57:05.551
I know everything that
goes on behind closed doors.

57:05.655 --> 57:07.689
I know all of the stories,

57:07.793 --> 57:12.000
but yours is the one that
gets me misty.

57:14.344 --> 57:15.551
You want special sauce
with that?

57:15.655 --> 57:17.000
- No.
- No?

57:17.103 --> 57:18.482
[inhales sharply]

57:18.586 --> 57:22.448
And now with your Aunt Barb
headed for assisted living

57:22.551 --> 57:24.344
over at Ridgecrest...

57:24.448 --> 57:27.620
She's the one who raised you.

57:27.724 --> 57:32.310
You're the only one left
holding the bag,

57:32.413 --> 57:37.448
expected to flip the coin
for that overpriced day camp,

57:37.551 --> 57:41.103
ten times the price of
a tropical vacation,

57:41.206 --> 57:43.034
and no pool.

57:45.068 --> 57:46.689
Hey, there, cowboy.

57:46.793 --> 57:51.137
I think you got yourself
in a bit of a situation.

57:51.241 --> 57:53.103
- What is this?

57:53.206 --> 57:56.448
What are you doing?
You've been studying me?

57:56.551 --> 58:00.344
- How much to put Barbie up
in Ridgecrest for a year?

58:00.448 --> 58:03.655
Depending on her insurance,
which I'm sure won't help much,

58:03.758 --> 58:08.379
you're looking at
about 30K a year.

58:08.482 --> 58:11.172
Done.
- What?

58:11.275 --> 58:13.655
- I got you covered.

58:13.758 --> 58:20.206
Three years, $100,000,

58:20.310 --> 58:21.793
a little extra scratch
on the side

58:21.896 --> 58:25.758
to do whatever
the fuck it is you do.

58:25.862 --> 58:27.275
If she doesn't live that long,
you got yourself

58:27.379 --> 58:29.793
some fuck-you money.

58:29.896 --> 58:32.689
She lives longer
than three years,

58:32.793 --> 58:35.827
well, I'm sure
we can work something out.

58:35.931 --> 58:36.965
Ketchup?

58:37.068 --> 58:40.206
- No.
Hold on, wait.

58:40.310 --> 58:42.275
[scoffs]

58:42.379 --> 58:45.310
You're willing
to just pay for this?

58:47.172 --> 58:48.931
- Consider it done.

58:49.034 --> 58:50.551
- You're gonna give me $100,000

58:50.655 --> 58:51.655
'cause you put a knife
to my throat?

58:51.758 --> 58:54.275
- Shh, ooh.

58:54.379 --> 58:57.931
Now, we agreed
to forget all that.

58:58.034 --> 59:01.344
Now, I'm not sure that
that is worth 100,000.

59:01.448 --> 59:04.482
What you're gonna do for me

59:04.586 --> 59:09.379
is gonna be much easier.

59:09.482 --> 59:12.241
- Do for you?

59:12.344 --> 59:16.517
♪

59:16.620 --> 59:17.965
Grant?

59:18.068 --> 59:19.241
- Where's the tickle stick?

59:19.344 --> 59:21.172
- What do you mean, do for you?

59:21.275 --> 59:23.034
- What do you think I mean?

59:23.137 --> 59:25.896
- I'm not sure.

59:26.000 --> 59:30.482
- I want you
to take care of her.

59:30.586 --> 59:32.620
- Holy shit.
- Hmm?

59:32.724 --> 59:36.310
- You got to be kidding me.

59:36.413 --> 59:41.103
You want me to kill your wife?
- [laughs]

59:41.206 --> 59:43.206
[laughing] I don't want you
to kill my wife.

59:43.310 --> 59:45.241
What the hell's
the matter with you?

59:45.344 --> 59:47.000
I want you to take her out,
go shopping,

59:47.103 --> 59:48.793
dinner, you know, whatever.

59:48.896 --> 59:50.241
- What?

59:50.344 --> 59:51.379
- I'm just ribbing you.

59:51.482 --> 59:55.551
Yeah, I--I mean,
I want you to kill her.

59:55.655 --> 1:00:00.034
Hey, check this out, bro.
Look at this.

1:00:00.137 --> 1:00:03.896
That's what two hours a day
at the gym gets you.

1:00:04.000 --> 1:00:05.793
If you got two hours
a day for ab toning,

1:00:05.896 --> 1:00:10.034
you got problems, right?

1:00:10.137 --> 1:00:12.758
People who are in shape
are fucked up.

1:00:12.862 --> 1:00:16.931
You know who's happy?
Fat people.

1:00:17.034 --> 1:00:19.000
There's just no reason
to fill a void

1:00:19.103 --> 1:00:21.965
that's never gonna get filled.

1:00:22.068 --> 1:00:24.344
You know when I'm
in the best shape,

1:00:24.448 --> 1:00:27.206
I feel like I'm just--
- Grant, don't do this, man.

1:00:27.310 --> 1:00:28.896
You know, I appreciate
the offer for my aunt,

1:00:29.000 --> 1:00:32.172
but dude, whatever problem
you think you have,

1:00:32.275 --> 1:00:34.724
just--just get a divorce.

1:00:34.827 --> 1:00:37.827
- Wayne,
I don't believe in divorce.

1:00:37.931 --> 1:00:38.896
- You know what?
I think you've had

1:00:39.000 --> 1:00:42.448
a little too much to drink.

1:00:42.551 --> 1:00:45.655
- You think so?

1:00:45.758 --> 1:00:47.068
- No one gets away with it.

1:00:47.172 --> 1:00:50.034
- Oh, yes, they do.

1:00:50.137 --> 1:00:52.413
Yes, they do.

1:00:52.517 --> 1:00:55.068
Wayne, 60% of murders

1:00:55.172 --> 1:00:58.310
are spouses killing spouses.

1:00:58.413 --> 1:01:00.379
You know who gets caught?

1:01:00.482 --> 1:01:02.413
These morons who
didn't think it through,

1:01:02.517 --> 1:01:05.758
whose emotions
got the best of them.

1:01:05.862 --> 1:01:06.965
Do you know how many murders

1:01:07.068 --> 1:01:09.034
there are every hour
in this country

1:01:09.137 --> 1:01:10.551
and what the percentage is
for the amount--

1:01:10.655 --> 1:01:12.931
- Stop.
Stop it.

1:01:13.034 --> 1:01:16.000
Listen, man, I think
you got me all wrong, okay?

1:01:16.103 --> 1:01:17.034
I'm not your man.

1:01:17.137 --> 1:01:18.310
I don't know why you think

1:01:18.413 --> 1:01:20.206
that I can do
something like that.

1:01:20.310 --> 1:01:21.379
- Shh.

1:01:21.482 --> 1:01:25.965
Because
you've already done the deed.

1:01:26.068 --> 1:01:27.034
You've already done it.

1:01:27.137 --> 1:01:29.655
- What does that mean?

1:01:29.758 --> 1:01:33.620
- You've killed people.
You understand?

1:01:33.724 --> 1:01:35.724
Now--listen.

1:01:35.827 --> 1:01:39.000
Now, you can say

1:01:39.103 --> 1:01:43.344
that it was
for God and country,

1:01:43.448 --> 1:01:45.793
but it's all the same, Wayne.

1:01:45.896 --> 1:01:49.344
And God and country didn't work
out so fucking hot, did it?

1:01:49.448 --> 1:01:54.310
That bullshit GI bill?

1:01:54.413 --> 1:01:56.896
Left to deal with your demons,

1:01:57.000 --> 1:02:00.206
still paying tax on that,
am I right?

1:02:00.310 --> 1:02:05.551
♪

1:02:05.655 --> 1:02:11.137
I'm talking about
something real.

1:02:11.241 --> 1:02:14.931
Cold, hard cash for you

1:02:15.034 --> 1:02:18.827
and a better life
for Aunt Barb.

1:02:18.931 --> 1:02:20.551
Now, that sounds
like a better deal

1:02:20.655 --> 1:02:23.827
than Uncle Sam's peddling,
don't you think?

1:02:23.931 --> 1:02:26.344
Huh?

1:02:28.827 --> 1:02:30.896
What's this?

1:02:35.241 --> 1:02:36.620
[doorbell chimes]

1:02:41.965 --> 1:02:44.551
Oh, he's new.

1:02:44.655 --> 1:02:46.586
Must be a personal trainer

1:02:46.689 --> 1:02:49.310
or some punk
who works at the mall,

1:02:49.413 --> 1:02:52.862
all dressed up
and smelling sweet.

1:02:52.965 --> 1:02:55.827
Pants are fucking gay.

1:02:55.931 --> 1:02:57.482
[soft brooding music]

1:02:57.586 --> 1:03:00.689
- Grant, you--
you have her on camera, man.

1:03:00.793 --> 1:03:03.068
Dude, if this goes any farther,
that's adultery.

1:03:03.172 --> 1:03:05.551
Think about this.
Use this.

1:03:05.655 --> 1:03:07.724
Dude, that--that would
kick her ass in divorce court.

1:03:07.827 --> 1:03:09.620
Shit, man, I'm no lawyer,
but I know that--

1:03:09.724 --> 1:03:11.965
[shatters]

1:03:12.068 --> 1:03:15.517
- Listen to me.

1:03:15.620 --> 1:03:18.241
It is not about
the fucking money.

1:03:18.344 --> 1:03:22.034
♪

1:03:22.137 --> 1:03:26.724
Now, it's not something

1:03:26.827 --> 1:03:31.344
that I can explain to you

1:03:31.448 --> 1:03:35.655
and probably not something
that you'd ever understand.

1:03:35.758 --> 1:03:38.413
But that's okay,

1:03:38.517 --> 1:03:43.241
because I'm not paying you
to make sense of it.

1:03:43.344 --> 1:03:48.172
♪

1:03:48.275 --> 1:03:51.379
[lighter flicking]

1:03:56.275 --> 1:03:58.965
We're talking about guarantees,

1:03:59.068 --> 1:04:02.413
no room for error.

1:04:04.827 --> 1:04:07.793
Ten days from now,
I go to Fort Lauderdale.

1:04:07.896 --> 1:04:10.137
I'm gonna do some fishing
with friends.

1:04:10.241 --> 1:04:11.551
Courtney won't be going...

1:04:11.655 --> 1:04:12.551
That's why I built this fucking
house for you!

1:04:12.655 --> 1:04:14.413
Never does.

1:04:14.517 --> 1:04:16.137
The day before I leave,

1:04:16.241 --> 1:04:18.103
I will start
an argument with her,

1:04:18.206 --> 1:04:19.965
telling her that I think
she's been drinking too much.

1:04:20.068 --> 1:04:21.310
Don't fucking need it!

1:04:21.413 --> 1:04:24.137
That won't be
a difficult one to start.

1:04:24.241 --> 1:04:25.344
During our little debate,

1:04:25.448 --> 1:04:26.965
I will pour out
the last of the wine

1:04:27.068 --> 1:04:29.241
we have in the house
just to show her who's boss.

1:04:29.344 --> 1:04:30.724
[indistinct shouting]

1:04:30.827 --> 1:04:33.724
One of her friends  will be around to overhear it,

1:04:33.827 --> 1:04:35.206
embarrassed that
she had to see it,

1:04:35.310 --> 1:04:37.241
but believe me,
she will see it.

1:04:37.344 --> 1:04:38.793
You're a drugged-out loony.

1:04:38.896 --> 1:04:40.896
- I have to be
to put up with this shit.

1:04:41.000 --> 1:04:42.620
- The day I go,

1:04:42.724 --> 1:04:46.379
she'll be at the liquor store

1:04:46.482 --> 1:04:49.034
refilling her supply.

1:04:49.137 --> 1:04:50.517
She'll be seen
on store security

1:04:50.620 --> 1:04:52.931
and have receipts
to back that up.

1:04:53.034 --> 1:04:55.172
That night
she'll have a few glasses

1:04:55.275 --> 1:04:57.724
before going out
with her friends.

1:04:57.827 --> 1:05:00.034
Her friends will tell her
that she drinks too much,

1:05:00.137 --> 1:05:02.137
because they always do.

1:05:02.241 --> 1:05:03.551
They'll tell her
that it's dangerous

1:05:03.655 --> 1:05:05.448
to mix booze with her pills,

1:05:05.551 --> 1:05:09.172
and she'll ignore them,
as she always has.

1:05:09.275 --> 1:05:12.344
[indistinct chatter]

1:05:16.034 --> 1:05:17.448
- All right, guys.
Let's have another one.

1:05:17.551 --> 1:05:20.448
[brooding music]

1:05:20.551 --> 1:05:27.586
♪

1:05:28.275 --> 1:05:30.517
- This...

1:05:30.620 --> 1:05:33.551
is buprenorphine.

1:05:33.655 --> 1:05:35.793
She's been taking these
for almost a year.

1:05:35.896 --> 1:05:39.586
Now, one a day gives her
a warm, zombie buzz.

1:05:39.689 --> 1:05:42.413
Ten would stop her heart.

1:05:42.517 --> 1:05:45.586
Her close friends, her family,
they all know she takes them,

1:05:45.689 --> 1:05:48.206
and they know that I oppose it.

1:05:50.275 --> 1:05:52.724
Take it.

1:05:52.827 --> 1:05:55.379
She'll wake up with a hangover.

1:05:55.482 --> 1:05:58.620
She will go to town,

1:05:58.724 --> 1:06:00.689
go shopping, have lunch,

1:06:00.793 --> 1:06:01.965
get her hair done...

1:06:02.068 --> 1:06:03.482
- [coughs]
- Coffee with friends.

1:06:03.586 --> 1:06:05.137
Maybe another round with

1:06:05.241 --> 1:06:08.482
that little boy
in the fag pants.

1:06:12.034 --> 1:06:14.448
I will be watching the house.

1:06:14.551 --> 1:06:17.413
When I know that she is gone,
I will send you a text.

1:06:17.517 --> 1:06:18.862
[phone chimes]

1:06:18.965 --> 1:06:21.827
And that is your signal
that it's all clear.

1:06:21.931 --> 1:06:23.379
You will go to my house.

1:06:23.482 --> 1:06:25.793
There's a spare key
on the rock ledge.

1:06:25.896 --> 1:06:27.310
You will fill the wine bottle

1:06:27.413 --> 1:06:30.827
with 150 milligrams
of buprenorphine.

1:06:30.931 --> 1:06:33.413
She won't taste it.

1:06:33.517 --> 1:06:37.413
You leave the house,
lock the door, leave the key,

1:06:37.517 --> 1:06:38.448
and be on your way.

1:06:38.551 --> 1:06:39.551
[lock clicks]

1:06:39.655 --> 1:06:42.379
It will take you five minutes,

1:06:42.482 --> 1:06:44.586
and that's if you
take your time.

1:06:44.689 --> 1:06:48.310
Courtney will drink
the entire bottle.

1:06:48.413 --> 1:06:52.793
She will doze off or pass out

1:06:52.896 --> 1:06:56.551
and be dead within an hour.

1:06:56.655 --> 1:06:59.620
It won't be painful.

1:06:59.724 --> 1:07:02.827
It's a feeling she's used to,

1:07:02.931 --> 1:07:05.862
drifting off into oblivion.

1:07:05.965 --> 1:07:07.310
Not a big stretch for her.

1:07:10.103 --> 1:07:13.344
The autopsy will show
what me and her family,

1:07:13.448 --> 1:07:16.931
and her friends already know.

1:07:17.034 --> 1:07:19.862
She played a dangerous game,

1:07:19.965 --> 1:07:22.896
drank too much,
took too many pills,

1:07:23.000 --> 1:07:25.965
and it caught up to her,

1:07:26.068 --> 1:07:30.827
the same way it did
her own mother 12 years ago.

1:07:30.931 --> 1:07:35.793
- Holy shit.

1:07:35.896 --> 1:07:38.034
- Of course,

1:07:38.137 --> 1:07:43.517
people will be shocked
but not surprised.

1:07:45.517 --> 1:07:47.896
I'll have to be devastated,

1:07:48.000 --> 1:07:51.862
shut myself down,
not be too social for a while,

1:07:51.965 --> 1:07:56.482
spend a year in mourning,
maybe more.

1:07:56.586 --> 1:08:01.896
But for you?
It's five minutes.

1:08:02.000 --> 1:08:04.931
Five minutes,

1:08:05.034 --> 1:08:08.586
and you'll make nearly triple
what you earn

1:08:08.689 --> 1:08:13.068
breaking your fucking back
for a year.

1:08:13.172 --> 1:08:15.137
Tax-free, bub.

1:08:15.241 --> 1:08:19.655
♪

1:08:19.758 --> 1:08:21.620
- How long you been
thinking about all this?

1:08:21.724 --> 1:08:24.310
- I don't know.

1:08:24.413 --> 1:08:26.000
I've left little seeds
here and there

1:08:26.103 --> 1:08:28.620
over the past few months,

1:08:28.724 --> 1:08:32.482
got on to her about
her drinking and her pills

1:08:32.586 --> 1:08:35.172
in front of her friends.

1:08:38.965 --> 1:08:41.793
- This is crazy.

1:08:41.896 --> 1:08:46.827
- Crazy people
don't plan this well.

1:08:53.068 --> 1:08:56.827
I'm sorry about your chow.

